arlioni/Scaroth in the ''[[Doctor Who]]'' story \"[[City of Death]]\" || [[Kevin Flood (actor)|Kevin Flood]] || \n|- \n| Higgins || from the 1951 radio comedy ''[[It's Higgins, Sir]]'', recreated as the television show ''[[Our Man Higgins]]'' in 1962 || Harry McNaughton, [[Stanley Holloway]] || MAGNUM PI had a butler named HIGGINS, played by JOHN HILLERMAN\n|- \n| Hillary || butler for [[Lara Croft]] in ''[[Lara Croft: Tomb Raider]]'' and ''[[Lara Croft Tomb Raider: The Cradle of Life]]'' || [[Chris Barrie]] || \n|-\n|Robert Hiller\n|Dorothy's butler in [[Two's Company (TV series)|Two's Company]]\n|[[Donald Sinden]]\n|\n|- \n| Hirsh || butler to [[WKRP]] owner Lillian Carlson || [[Ian Wolfe]] || \n|- \n| Hobson || in ''[[Arthur (1981 film)|Arthur]]'' and ''[[Arthur 2: On the Rocks]]'' || [[John Gielgud]] || \n|- \n| Hovis || from ''[[Catscratch]]'' || [[Maurice LaMarche]] || \n|- \n| Angus Hudson || from ''[[Upstairs, Downstairs (1971 TV series)|Upstairs, Downstairs]]'' ||[[Gordon Jackson (actor)|Gordon Jackson]] || \n|- \n| [[Ianto Jones]] || from ''[[Torchwood]]'' (while his role could be considered General Support, he considers that the services he provides make him \"like a butler\") || || \n|- \n| Ingmar || ''[[Freakazoid]]'''s mute butler || || \n|- \n| Igor || butler to ''[[Count Duckula]]'' (animated series) ||[[Jack May]] || \n|-\n| [[Igor (Young Frankenstein)|Igor]] ||The hunchbacked assistant of Dr. Frederick Frankenstein in ''[[Young Frankenstein]]'' || [[Marty Feldman]]||\n|- \n| Ishizaki || [[Karin Kanzuki]]'s rotund, muscular butler in ''[[Street Fighter Alpha 3]]'' || || \n|- \n| Jacob || the unisex butler in all the ''[[La Cage aux Folles (film)|La Cage Aux Folles]]'' films  || [[Benny Luke]] || \n|- \n| Jake || witch disguised as the Wilhern family's butler in ''[[Penelope (2008 film)|Penelope]]'' || [[Michael Feast]] || \n|- \n| Jakob || the avatar's butler in ''[[Fire Emblem Fates]]'' || [[Benjamin Diskin]], [[Junichi Suwabe]]\n|\n|-\n| James || 