k Price (actor)|Mark Price]], [[Jason Wooten]] || \n|- \n| Riffael Raffit || in ''[[Godchild]]'' || || \n|- \n| Riffael Valentine || Butler for Lucien Ebanezer of the Ebanezer Household in Kuroshitsuji III fanmade || || \n|- \n| Rihito Shibata || Mei Shinonome's Butler from ''[[Mei-chan no Shitsuji]] || [[Hiro Mizushima]] (live action) || \n|- \n| Rochester ||butler to [[Jack Benny]] on the ''[[Jack Benny Show]]'' ||   || \n|- \n| Rogers || husband of Ethel Rogers and suspect in [[Agatha Christie]]'s ''[[And Then There Were None]]'' || [[Richard Haydn]], [[Paul L. Smith]] || \n|-  \n| Rowen J. Ilbert || Butler for the Sharil family in the video game ''[[Tales of Xillia]]'' || [[Mughito|Mugihito Terada]] (Japanese), [[Todd Haberkorn]] (English) ||\n|- \n| Ruthven || Butler to [[Melrose Plant]] in the [[Richard Jury]] detective series written by [[Martha Grimes]] (pronounced ''Rivven'') ||  ||\n|-\n| Sam || Butler and best friend to Rick Blaine || [[Dooley Wilson]], [[Clarence Muse]], [[Scatman Crothers]] || \n|-\n| Sam || Butler to the Amberson family || [[J. Louis Johnson]], [[Eamon Rohan]] || \n|-\n|[[Samwise Gamgee]]\n|Gardener, companion, and manservant to [[Frodo Baggins]] in [[The Lord of the Rings|Lord of the Rings]]\n|[[Sean Astin]] ([[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|live action]]), [[Roddy McDowall]] ([[The Return of the King (1980 film)|animated version of Return of the King]]), Michael Scholes ([[The Lord of the Rings (1978 film)|animated version of Lord of the Rings]])\n|\n|-\n| Saturnin || Butler/servant in [[Zdenek Jirotka]]'s [[Saturnin (novel)|eponymous novell]] and eponymous film|| [[Old\u0159ich V\u00edzner]] || \n|-\n| Sandor || Butler/servant to Countess Marya Zaleska || [[Irving Pichel]] ||\n|-\n| Saunders || the butler who replaced Benson DuBois on ''[[Soap (TV series)|Soap]]'' || [[Roscoe Lee Browne]] || \n|- \n| [[Sebastian Beach]] || [[Lord Emsworth]]'s butler at [[Blandings Castle]], from the works of [[P. G. Wodehouse]] || || \n|- \n| Sebastian || [[Lili (Tekken)|Lili's]] butler in ''[[Tekken 5: Dark Resurrection]]'' || || \n|- \n| [[List of Black Butler characters#Sebastian Michaelis|Sebastian Michaelis]] || butler to Ciel Phantomhive in the manga ''[[Kuroshitsuji]]'' || [[Daisuke Ono]] (Japanese), [[J. Michael Tatum]] (English), [[Hiro Mizushima]] (Live action) ||  \n|- \n| Seecombe || Butler to the Ambrose family || [[Tudor Owen (actor)|Tudor Owen]], [[Bert Parnaby]], [[Tim Barlow]] || \n|-\n| Shakelford || from ''[http://www.slightlywarped.com/justicesquad/ Justice Squad]'' and ''[[The Critic]]'' || || \n|- \n| Shinobu || Shiori Hongo's Butler from ''[[Mei-chan no Shitsuji]] || [[Osamu Mukai]] (live action) || \n|- \n| Silversmith || butler of Deverill Hall in ''[[The Mating Season (novel)|The Mating Season]]'' || || \n|- \n| Simonides || Butler to [[Judah Ben-Hur]] || [[Nigel De Brulier]], [[Sam Jaffe]], [[Sim\u00f3n Andreu]], [[Haluk Bilginer]] ||\n|- \n| Smethells || steward for the player in ''[[Titanic: Adventure Out of Time]]'' || || \n|- \n| Smithers || [[Veronica Lodge]]'s butler in the [[Archie Comics|Archie]] comics || || \n|- \n| Spencer || the Hartfords' butler in ''[[Power Rangers Operation Overdrive]]'' || || \n|- \n| Septimus Spratt || butler to Violet Crawley, the Dowager Countess of Grantham, in the ITV series ''[[Downton Abbey]]'' || [[Jeremy Swift]] || \n|-\n| Standish || butler to [[T. Herman Zweibel]], editor of ''[[The Onion]]'' || || \n|- \n| Stevens || in ''[[Remains of the Day]]'' || [[Anthony Hopkins]] || \n|- \n| Stokes || butler in the sitcom ''[[You rang m'lord|You Rang M'Lord]]'' || [[Paul Shane]] || \n|- \n| Subaru Konoe || female butler of Kanade Suzutsuki who is disguised as a male in the ''[[Mayo Chiki! ]]'' anime, manga and light novel || ''[[Yuka Iguchi]] || \n|- \n| Tanaka || former head butler of the Phantomhive household in the manga Kuroshitsuji.'' || || \n|- \n| Thomas || Butler to the Lord family  || [[Rex Evans]], [[Richard Garrick]] || \n|- \n| Thoma