ost-season appearance, post-season series win, [[Stanley Cup]] Finals and Stanley Cup streaks up to and including the [[2018\u201319 NHL season]] and subsequent [[2019 Stanley Cup playoffs]]. These lists do not include the canceled [[2004\u201305 NHL season]]. \n\n==Longest active streaks==\n\n===Post-season appearance streaks===\n\n<!-- NOTE: Please do not update this table *until the end of the current NHL season* (even if 'your' team has already mathematically 'made' it!) in order to have *all* the data for *all* the teams consistent (for instance a team may not make the playoffs until the last day of the season). Wikipedia's purpose is not to provide up-to-the-minute statistics. -->\n\nA post-season appearance streak is continued by making the NHL playoffs in consecutive years after the regular season. Since the first round of the playoffs consists of 8 series, there will always be 16 teams in this list (of the 31 teams in the NHL). {{further information|List of NHL franchise post-season droughts}}\n\n<!--{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2|Key\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffffcc; width:20px;\"|\n|align=left|Teams that are mathematically eliminated from continuing their appearance streaks through the 2017-18 season.\n|}-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" width=\"180pt\" | Team\n! width=\"90pt\" | Post-season streak\n! width=\"180pt\" | Last missed post-season\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Stanley Cup Championships during streak\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span> 13 seasons || [[2005\u201306 Pittsburgh Penguins season|2005\u201306]] || align=\"left\" | 3 : [[2008\u201309 Pittsburgh Penguins season|2008\u201309]], [[2015\u201316 Pittsburgh Penguins season|2015\u201316]], [[2016\u201317 Pittsburgh Penguins season|2016\u201317]]\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Nashville Predators]] || 5 seasons || [[2013\u201314 Nashville Predators season|2013\u201314]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Washington Capitals]] || 5 seasons || [[2013\u201314 Washington Capitals season|2013\u201314]] || align=\"left\" | 1 : [[2017\u201318 Washington Capitals season|2017\u201318]]\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[San Jose Sharks]] || 4 seasons || [[2014\u201315 San Jose Sharks season|2014\u201315]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Boston Bruins]] || 3 seasons || [[2015\u201316 Boston Bruins season|2015\u201316]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Columbus Blue Jackets]] || 3 seasons || [[2015\u201316 Columbus Blue Jackets season|2015\u201316]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Toronto Maple Leafs]] || 3 seasons || [[2015\u201316 Toronto Maple Leafs season|2015\u201316]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Colorado Avalanche]] || 2 seasons || [[2016\u201317 Colorado Avalanche season|2016\u201317]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Tampa Bay Lightning]] || 2 seasons || [[2016\u201317 Tampa Bay Lightning season|2016\u201317]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Vegas Golden Knights]] || 2 seasons || never (inception of franchise in [[2017\u201318 NHL season|2017\u201318]]) ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Winnipeg Jets]] || 2 seasons || [[2016\u201317 Winnipeg Jets season|2016\u201317]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Calgary Flames]] || 1 season || [[2017\u201318 Calgary Flames season|2017\u201318]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Carolina Hurricanes]] || 1 season || [[2017\u201318 Carolina Hurricanes season|2017\u201318]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Dallas Stars]] || 1 season || [[2017\u201318 Dallas Stars season|2017\u201318]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[New York Islanders]] || 1 season || [[2017\u201318 New York Islanders season|2017\u201318]] ||\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[St. Louis Blues]] || 1 season || [[2017\u201318 St. Louis Blues season|2017\u201318]] || align=\"left\" | 1 : [[2018\u201319 St. Louis Blues season|2018\u201319]]\n|}\n\n===Post-season series win streaks===\n\nThis is a list of teams that have active post-season series win streaks. A post-season series win streak is continued by making the post-season and winning at least the first round series of the playoffs. Since the first round of the playoffs consists of 16 teams in 8 series, there will always be 8 teams in this list, the winners of those series.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" width=\"180pt\" | Team\n! width=\"90pt\" | Post-season series win streak\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Boston Bruins]] || 2 seasons\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[San Jose Sharks]] || 2 seasons\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Carolina Hurricanes]] || 1 season\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Colorado Avalanche]] || 1 season\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Columbus Blue Jackets]] || 1 season\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Dallas Stars]] || 1 season\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[New York Islanders]] || 1 season\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[St. Louis Blues]] || 1 season\n|-\n|}\n\n==Longest all-time streaks==\n\n===Post-season appearance streaks===\n\nThis section has been updated to include teams who appeared in the [[2019 Stanley Cup playoffs]].\n\n{{legend|#CFECEC|Active franchise streak is highlighted|border=#AAAAAA}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" width=\"180pt\" | Team\n! width=\"90pt\" | Post-season streak\n! width=\"180pt\" | Consecutive post-season appearances\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Stanley Cup Championships during streak\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Boston Bruins]] || 29 seasons<sup>1</sup> || [[1967\u201368 Boston Bruins season|1967\u201368]] through to [[1995\u201396 Boston Bruins season|1995\u201396]] || align=\"left\" | 2 : [[1969\u201370 Boston Bruins season|1969\u201370]], [[1971\u201372 Boston Bruins season|1971\u201372]]\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | [[Chicago Black Hawks|Chicago Blackhawks]]<sup>2</sup> || 28 seasons || [[1969\u201370 Chicago Black Hawks season|1969\u201370]] through to [[1996\u201397 Chicago Blackhawks season|1996\u201397]] || align=\"left\" | none\n|-\n| align=